: null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.lower", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.upper", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.replace", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.ljust", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.rjust", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.lstrip", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.rstrip", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.center", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.strip", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.translate", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.expandtabs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.swapcase", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.zfill", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.casefold", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.removeprefix", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "markupsafe.Markup.removesuffix", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A string that is ready to be safely inserted into an HTML or XML\ndocument, either because it was escaped or because it was marked\nsafe.\n\nPassing an object to the constructor converts it to text and wraps\nit to mark it safe without escaping. To escape the text, use the\n{meth}`escape` class method instead.\n\n```pycon\n>>> Markup(\"Hello, <em>World</em>!\")\nMarkup('Hello, <em>World</em>!')\n>>> Markup(42)\nMarkup('42')\n>>> Markup.escape(\"Hello, <em>World</em>!\")\nMarkup('Hello &lt;em&gt;World&lt;/em&gt;!')\n```\n\nThis implements the `__html__()` interface that some frameworks\nuse. Passing an object that implements `__html__()` will wrap the\noutput of that method, marking it safe.\n\n```pycon\n>>> 